    "description": "Costa Coffee India is actively seeking a talented and motivated Department Manager to join our dynamic team in Surat. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Costa Coffee India:\nCosta Coffee India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage store operations to ensure smooth daily functioning\n• Maintain high standards of store hygiene and cleanliness\n• Ensure visual merchandising standards are maintained at all times\n• Build relationships with regular customers to drive loyalty\n• Prepare daily sales reports and share insights with management\n• Coordinate with the supply chain team for timely stock delivery\n• Ensure compliance with company policies and retail regulations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Planogram\n• Proficiency in E-commerce Integration\n• Proficiency in POS Systems\n• Proficiency in Inventory Management\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n• Proficiency in Retail Operations\n• Proficiency in Loss Prevention\n• Proficiency in Visual Merchandising\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Surat, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Costa Coffee India!",
